The Definition of Kinetic Energy

The kinetic energy of an object is proportional to the mass of that object and its speed squared.

K = \frac{1}{2} m v^{2}

where:

K [var. scal. KineticEnergy, M L^{2} T^{-2}, kg m^{2} s^{-2}] is the kinetic energy of the object
m [var. scal. Mass, M, kg] is the mass of the object
v [var. scal. Speed, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the speed of the object

variants:

In terms of momentum

K = \frac{p^{2}}{2m}

